abstract: The South Carolina primary is certain to be a fork in the road for Democrats’ 2020 presidential nominating contest. But there’s no reliable map showing where voters’ choices might lead once the state's voters — the first 2020 contest where black voters hold the strongest sway — have their say.

lead_paragraph: SPARTANBURG, S.C. — The South Carolina primary is certain to be a fork in the road for Democrats’ 2020 presidential nominating contest. But there’s no reliable map showing where voters’ choices might lead once the state's voters — the first 2020 contest where black voters hold the strongest sway — have their say.
headline_main: Key Questions Heading Into South Carolina Democratic Primary
headline_print_headline: Key Questions Heading Into South Carolina Democratic Primary

abstract: Many black voters rallied around Joe Biden in Saturday’s primary, eager to send a message that their views of electability are not shaped by predominantly white states like Iowa.
snippet: Many black voters rallied around Joe Biden in Saturday’s primary, eager to send a message that their views of electability are not shaped by predominantly white states like Iowa.
lead_paragraph: NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. — In 2008 and 2016, black voters in South Carolina’s presidential primary set the last two Democratic nominees on their way, backing Barack Obama and Hillary Clinton by huge margins. Rival candidates never managed to catch up in the race for delegates to clinch the nomination.

abstract: Many listeners would never repeat what these podcast hosts say. So why do they desperately want to hear from them?
snippet: Many listeners would never repeat what these podcast hosts say. So why do they desperately want to hear from them?
lead_paragraph: IOWA CITY — The people in the crowd were angry, and “Chapo Trap House” wanted them to stay that way. The five hosts of the popular socialist podcast wanted everyone to know they had all been lied to. About everything.

abstract: After a quiet decade and a painful divorce, the singer has a new studio album, a whole new set of fans and a favorite 2020 candidate. (His name is Pete.)

lead_paragraph: As they neared the turn of the millennium, and steeled themselves for the Y2K bug, Americans faced a critical question: Whom would they crown the teen queen of pop?

headline_main: What’s at Stake in the South Carolina Primary
byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Adriana Ramić

abstract: Joe Biden scored a thundering victory Saturday in South Carolina’s Democratic primary on the strength of African American support, a decisive win that could force moderate rivals out of the race and blunt the rise of progressive leader Bernie Sanders.
snippet: Joe Biden scored a thundering victory Saturday in South Carolina’s Democratic primary on the strength of African American support, a decisive win that could force moderate rivals out of the race and blunt the rise of progressive leader Bernie Sand...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Joe Biden scored a thundering victory Saturday in South Carolina’s Democratic primary on the strength of African American support, a decisive win that could force moderate rivals out of the race and blunt the rise of progressive leader Bernie Sanders.
headline_main: Biden Wins South Carolina, Aims for Super Tuesday Momentum
headline_print_headline: Biden Wins South Carolina, Aims for Super Tuesday Momentum

abstract: Readers share their choice for president and how it has changed in recent weeks.
snippet: Readers share their choice for president and how it has changed in recent weeks.
lead_paragraph: This Tuesday is the big one — Super Tuesday, when 14 states, and American Samoa, will vote in Democratic primaries and caucuses. We recently asked our columnists to make their best cases for the six strongest Democratic candidates.
